{% comment %}
  Affiliate / agent referral tracking snippet
  ===========================================

  WHAT THIS IS
  ------------
  Drop this snippet into your Shopify theme (e.g. paste into theme.liquid before
  </body>, or include it from a snippet) to load the storefront affiliate
  tracking script. The script captures the `ref` and `agent_click_id` URL
  parameters set by the app's affiliate redirect, persists them (localStorage +
  a first-party cookie that survives Safari ITP), and writes them onto the
  Shopify cart note_attributes so the order webhook can attribute the sale.

  REQUIRED METAFIELD — custom.growth_agent_app_url
  ------------------------------------------------
  This snippet reads `shop.metafields.custom.growth_agent_app_url` to know the
  base URL of the analytics app (where affiliate-ref-tracking.js is served).
  That metafield MUST be set on the shop, or the <script src> resolves to an
  empty/invalid URL and tracking will silently not load.

  Set the value to the app's base URL, e.g.
      https://shopifyappanalytics.onrender.com
  (no trailing slash). The script path "/shopify/affiliate-ref-tracking.js" is
  appended automatically below.

  HOW TO SET IT (Shopify Admin)
  -----------------------------
  1. Shopify Admin → Settings → Custom data → Shop (under "Metafields").
  2. Add definition with:
       - Namespace and key: custom.growth_agent_app_url
       - Type: URL
  3. Save the definition, then set the value for your shop to the app base URL
     (e.g. https://shopifyappanalytics.onrender.com).

  After saving, reload the storefront and confirm the network tab shows
  /shopify/affiliate-ref-tracking.js loading from your app URL.
{% endcomment %}
<script>
  window.AFFILIATE_TRACKING_APP_URL = '{{ shop.metafields.custom.growth_agent_app_url | escape }}';
</script>
<script src="{{ shop.metafields.custom.growth_agent_app_url }}/shopify/affiliate-ref-tracking.js" defer></script>
